  "texts": [
    "DRaFT-Q is trained under low-VRAM conditions (T4 and L40S GPUs), reflecting realistic usage scenarios.",
    "Each dataset-specific accuracy metric is computed over held-out validation sets, and evaluation loss is averaged per-token using cross-entropy.",
    "DRaFT-Q's key advantage is its dynamic nature: by assigning rank adaptively and weighing losses based on token criticality, it learns faster and more effectively under the same hardware constraints.",
    "In GSM8K, this is reflected in higher EM accuracy; in CommonsenseQA and OpenBookQA, DRaFT-Q captures subtle semantic or factual cues more reliably.",
    "This makes DRaFT-Q not just competitive, but in some tasks, decisively better than fixed-rank PEFT methods even without additional parameter overhead."
